    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Elizabeth Arden to Open Day Spa in The Westchester</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Merri Rosenberg</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rosenberg, Merri</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Elizabeth Arden cosmetics firm plans to open day spa at The Westchester mall in White Plains, NY, in early 2000 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Elizabeth Arden, the cosmetics company, will open a day spa at The Westchester mall in White Plains early next year. The spa, known as the Red Door Salon and Spa, will offer hair and skin care products and services, including facials, massages and makeovers. It will join the company's other day spas in Manhattan, Chicago, Phoenix, Dallas and San Francisco.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Elizabeth Arden, the cosmetics company, will open a day spa at The Westchester mall in White Plains early next year. The spa, known as the Red Door Salon and Spa, will offer hair and skin care products and services, including facials, massages and makeovers. It will join the company's other day spas in Manhattan, Chicago, Phoenix, Dallas and San Francisco.</p>
        <p>''We thought it was a great location,'' said Dina Keenan, director of marketing for Elizabeth Arden Salons. ''And the demographics of The Westchester married nicely with our market. Some customers may prefer the city, and some want to go to a spa and salon that's close to their homes.''</p>
        <p>Merri Rosenberg</p>
        <p>IN BUSINESS</p>
      </block>
